      <body>In rails3 :as option can be used to map to a different controller. 

@@@ ruby
resources :photos, :as =&gt; &quot;images&quot;
@@@

Now /photos	will map to  images_path


The option you are looking for is :path. 

@@@ ruby
resources :posts, :path =&gt; :widgets
@@@</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In rails3 :as option can be used to map to a different
controller.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;resources :photos, :as =&amp;gt; &quot;images&quot;&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now /photos will map to images_path&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The option you are looking for is :path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;resources :posts, :path =&amp;gt; :widgets&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
